<hr color="#660066" size="20"><a id="fus_45" name=""><br>
<div align="center">
<center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" width="80%">
<tr>
<td width="100%">
<font size="2" color="#FFFFFF">April 21st, 2004</font><font size="2"> - 04-24-2004 06:51</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">Headlines&#33;<br>- Boat Gnomes are now available all the time. (and I thought gnomes were only good as appetizers)<br>- A new edition of the newspaper is available in your home town. Come and get it&#33;<br>- Auto Stand is now an option&#33;<br><br>Boat gnomes<br>----------------------<br><br>The boat gnomes and other alternate means of travel are now available. During this period of gnome servitude, the boats will be in drydock and receiving some much needed repairs.<br><br>Auto Stand<br>----------------------<br>You can now set your options to allow you to auto-stand when you attempt to move while sitting. You can find this under the options menu in-game. (alt-o)<br><br>Items <br>----------------------<br>Items that have procs should now show the level at which they will begin to proc.<br><br>Collision<br>----------------------<br>There should be some noticable improvements to collision.</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">- <a href="mailto:ronaldor@magecompendium.com">Ronaldor Vladimir</a></font><br><br></td>
</tr>
</table>
</center>
</div>

<hr color="#660066" size="20"><a id="fus_44" name=""><br>
<div align="center">
<center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" width="80%">
<tr>
<td width="100%">
<font size="2" color="#FFFFFF">April 7th, 2004</font><font size="2"> - 04-11-2004 09:21</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">The Graveyard zone, Shadowrest, is now live&#33;<br><br>We have introduced the new graveyard zone, Shadowrest, to the live servers.  The zone will allow adventurers whose corpse has decayed, after 7 days, to retrieve it.  They will merely have to greet the appropriate NPC in one of the following zones to activate their transport to Shadowrest;<br><br>East Commonlands<br>The Plane of Knowledge<br>Toxxulia Forest<br>Qeynos Hills<br>The Feerrott<br>Butcherblock Mountains<br>The Field of Bone<br>Shadeweavers Thicket<br>Misty Thicket<br><br>We hope you enjoy this new addition to EverQuest&#33;<br><br>The EverQuest Team</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">- <a href="mailto:ronaldor@magecompendium.com">Ronaldor Vladimir</a></font><br><br></td>
</tr>
